<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6876] Remove unused legacy scripts.conf</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6876</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some of the example collections include &lt;b&gt;scripts.conf&lt;/b&gt; in the &lt;b&gt;conf&lt;/b&gt; directory. It is not used by anything in the distribution and is somehow left over from the Solr 1.x legacy days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to safe delete it to avoid confusing users trying to understand what different files actually do.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12763128">SOLR-6876</key>
            <summary>Remove unused legacy scripts.conf</summary>
